{{Expand Portuguese|Francisco de Melo (bispo)|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | honorific-prefix = Most Reverend | name = Francisco de Melo | title = Bishop of Goa | other_names = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Goa and Daman|Diocese of Goa]] | see = | term = 1533–1536 | predecessor = None | successor = [[João de Albuquerque]] <!-- Orders --> | ordination = | ordained_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | cardinal = | created_cardinal_by = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = 27 Apr 1536 | death_place = [[Evora]], [[Portugal]] | previous_post = | nationality = | religion = | ethnicity = }}
'''Francisco de Melo''' (died 1536) was a Roman Catholic prelate who was named as the first [[Bishop of Goa]] (1533–1536).<ref name=HierarchiaIII-Goa>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/hierarchiacathol03eube#page/204/mode/2up|first=Konrad|last=Eubel|title=Hierarchia catholica medii et recentioris aevi |volume=Vol. III|pages=204|date=1923|publisher=Libreria Regensbergiana|location=Münster|edition=second|ISBN=}} ''(in Latin)''</ref>
==Biography== On 31 Jan 1533, Francisco de Melo was appointed during the papacy of [[Pope Clement VII]] as the first [[Bishop of Goa]].<ref name=HierarchiaIII-Goa /><ref name=CathHierFranMello>{{Cite web|last=Cheney |first=David M.|authorlink=|title=Bishop Francisco de Mello |publisher=''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''|date=|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bdmellof.html |accessdate=June 16, 2018}}{{Self-published source|date=July 2018}}</ref> He never took possession of the diocese as he died in [[Evora]], [[Portugal]] prior to his departure on 27 Apr 1536.<ref name=HierarchiaIII-Goa /><ref name=CathHierFranMello /><ref>{{Cite web|last= |first=|authorlink=|title=Former Bishops and Archbishops |publisher=''Archdiocese of Goa and Daman''|date=|url=http://www.archgoadaman.org/past-bishops |accessdate=June 16, 2018}}</ref>
