{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Use British English|date=March 2015}} {{For|the Church of England suffragan bishop|Anglican Bishop of Nottingham}} {{Infobox Bishopric |border = catholic |font_color = black |bishopric = [[Nottingham]] |coatofarms = |image = <!-- Image of the current incumbent --> |incumbent = [[Patrick McKinney]] |province = [[Province of Westminster|Westminster]] |diocese = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Nottingham|Nottingham]] |cathedral = [[Nottingham Cathedral]] |first_bishop = [[Joseph William Hendren|Joseph Hendren]] |date = 29 September 1850 |website = }} The '''Bishop of Nottingham''' is the [[Ordinary (officer)|Ordinary]] of the [[Roman Catholic]] [[Diocese of Nottingham]] in the [[Province of Westminster]].<ref name=dnott>{{Catholic-hierarchy|diocese|dnott|Diocese of Nottingham|2 July 2011}}</ref><ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/nott0.htm ''Diocese of Nottingham''] at GCatholic.org.com. Retrieved on 14 June 2011.</ref>
The diocese covers an area of {{convert|13074|km2|sqmi|-2|abbr=on}} and spans the counties of [[Derbyshire]] (excluding the [[High Peak, Derbyshire|High Peak]] and [[Chesterfield]] districts), [[Leicestershire]], [[Lincolnshire]], [[Nottinghamshire]] (excluding the district of [[Bassetlaw]]) and [[North Lincolnshire]]. The [[Episcopal see|see]] is in the [[Nottingham|City of Nottingham]] where the [[Cathedra|bishop's seat]] is located at the [[Nottingham Cathedral|Cathedral Church of St. Barnabas, Nottingham]].
The Diocese of Nottingham was erected on 29 September 1850, mainly from out of the [[Vicar Apostolic of the Central District|Vicariate Apostolic of the Central District]], and partly from the [[Vicar Apostolic of the Eastern District (England)|Eastern District]]. == List of the Bishops of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Nottingham, England == {| class="wikitable" style="width:95%"; border="1" ! colspan="4" style="background-color: #7F1734; color: white;"|Roman Catholic Bishops of Nottingham |-align=center ! style="background-color:#D4B1BB" width="9%"|From ! style="background-color:#D4B1BB" width="9%"|Until ! style="background-color:#D4B1BB" width="32%"|Incumbent ! style="background-color:#D4B1BB" width="45%"|Notes |- valign=top bgcolor="white" |align="center"|1851 |align="center"|1853 | [[Joseph William Hendren|'''Joseph''' William '''Hendren''']], [[Order of Friars Minor|O.F.M.]] | Previously [[Bishop of Clifton]] (1850–1851). [[Appointment of Catholic bishops|Appointed]] Bishop of Nottingham on 22 June 1851 and installed on 2 December 1851. Resigned on 23 February 1853 and appointed Titular Bishop of Martyropolis. Died on 14 November 1866.<ref name=bhend>{{Catholic-hierarchy|bishop|bhend|Bishop Joseph William Hendren, O.F.M.|2 July 2011}}</ref> |-valign=top bgcolor="#F7F0F2" |align="center"|1853 |align="center"|1874 | [[Richard Roskell|'''Richard''' Butler '''Roskell''']] | Appointed bishop on 29 July 1853 and consecrated on 21 September 1853. Resigned in 1874 and appointed Titular Bishop of Abdera on 5 July 1875. Died on 27 January 1883.<ref name=brosk>{{Catholic-hierarchy|bishop|brosk|Bishop Richard Butler Roskell|2 July 2011}}</ref> |- valign=top bgcolor="white" |align="center"|1874 |align="center"|1902 | [[Edward Gilpin Bagshawe|'''Edward''' Gilpin '''Bagshawe''']], [[Oratory of Saint Philip Neri|C.O.]] | Appointed bishop on 12 October 1874 and consecrated on 12 November 1874. Resigned on 18 January 1902. Appointed Titular Bishop of Hypaepa on 18 January 1902 an